<br>
If you have 4 or 5 wizards there, and are all in the same group, pick a mob, and start early and have everyone chain cast.  If you are the proper levels, the mob will be dead before it can kill any of you, and you won't lose so much mana that you can get good XP.<br>
<br>
If you have multiple wizards spread out, then coordinate, learn the damage output of the others at the raid, and kick ass, just trying to keep yourself from getting agroed to death.<br>
<br>
Now, the thing to avoid, having the mob run after you.  If the mob runs after you, that is time the tanks won't be doing damage to the mob.  So, if you are brave, get close to the tanks(not the mob), and that way if the mob DOES agro on you, you won't cause the melee classes to run far(if anywhere), to continue beating on the mobs.<br>
<br>
Those are just some ideas for you based on my 58 levels of experience.  Many will say nuke once or twice, some will say to chain cast, but it's all a matter of style.  As long as you don't make the healers heal you too often(you dont' want to &quot;waste their mana&quot;), and as long as you don't get yourself or others killed, a certain amount of agro will get you noticed.  I've personally found that if you can agro it so it hits you once or twice, then goes back to the tanks, you will show you have decent agro control.  That also shows you arn't sitting on your butt while the melees do the majority of the damage.  It's all about perception.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 58 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
